cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.CC 

The paper deals with permutation codes and their generalization to multipermutation codes, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The Ulam metric, which is the focus of the paper, is a measure of distance between permutations and is related to combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The analysis of sphere sizes for multipermutations also involves statistical inference (cs.SI).
